<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="374" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[491,1567,472,1665]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[531,662,610,634]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">Description</emphasis>
— Male: Idiosoma dorsally 360 long and 300 wide, ventrally 373 long. Gnathosomal bay shallow. Dorsal shield incomplete, 247 wide; distance dorsal shield – anterior idiosoma margin 48. Dorsum posterolaterally with small, rounded extensions. Cauda very short, not set off from anterior part of idiosoma; one pair of glandularia on cauda with short, forked setae. Medial margins of fourth coxae reduced to angles. Gonopore 28 long; genital plates long, extending to lateral idiosoma margin. Posterior to genital plates a pair of glandularia. Lengths of P1-5: 20, 64, 40, 64, 24. Palp rotated, P2 with two setae near ventral margin, P4 with a stout ventral seta ending in a hook-like tip. Length of I-leg-4-6: 60, 70, 80. Length of IV-leg-4-6: 74, 84, 86.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="374" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[491,1567,472,1665]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[531,640,920,944]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">Remarks</emphasis>
— According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Lundblad, O." box="[831,1013,919,943]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" pagination="1 - 86" refId="ref7736" refString="Lundblad, O. 1930. Sudamerikanische Hydracarinen. Zugleich Revision einiger von E. Daday aus Paraguay beschriebenen Arten. Zool. Bidr. Uppsala, 13: 1 - 86." type="journal article" year="1930">Lundblad (1930)</bibRefCitation>
, who examined the 
<typeStatus box="[1235,1290,920,944]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">types</typeStatus>
<emphasis box="[1293,1312,919,943]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">A</emphasis>
of. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Daday, 1905" authorityYear="1905" baseAuthorityName="Daday" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[1321,1501,919,943]" class="Arachnida" family="Arrenuridae" genus="Arrenurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minimus">
<emphasis box="[1321,1411,920,943]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">minimus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Daday, E. von" box="[1424,1501,919,943]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" pagination="1 - 374" refId="ref7639" refString="Daday, E. von 1905. Untersuchungen uber die Susswasser-Mikrofauna Paraguays. Mit einem Anhang: Zur Kenntnis der Naididen von Dr. W. Michaelsen. Zoologica, 18: 1 - 374." type="journal article" year="1905">Daday,</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
1905) and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Daday, 1905)" baseAuthorityName="Daday" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[607,891,953,977]" class="Arachnida" family="Arrenuridae" genus="Arrenurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundus">
<emphasis box="[607,731,953,977]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">A. rotundus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Daday, E. von" box="[746,884,953,977]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" pagination="1 - 374" refId="ref7639" refString="Daday, E. von 1905. Untersuchungen uber die Susswasser-Mikrofauna Paraguays. Mit einem Anhang: Zur Kenntnis der Naididen von Dr. W. Michaelsen. Zoologica, 18: 1 - 374." type="journal article" year="1905">Daday, 1905</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, the two species can be separated based on the pair of glandularia anterior and posterior of the genital plates. In 
<emphasis box="[1119,1209,989,1012]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">minimus</emphasis>
the anterior pair is more separated than the posterior pair, in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Daday" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[918,1011,1022,1046]" class="Arachnida" family="Arrenuridae" genus="Arrenurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundus">
<emphasis box="[918,1011,1022,1046]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">rotundus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it’s the other way around. In my collection from 
<collectingCountry box="[552,645,1057,1081]" name="Suriname" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">Surinam</collectingCountry>
, the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Koenike" authorityYear="1907" box="[698,809,1057,1081]" class="Arachnida" family="Arrenuridae" genus="Dadayella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[698,809,1057,1081]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">Dadayella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
females show a large variation in the distance of these pairs of glandularia. In my opinion this characteristic is not suitable for species delimitation. The 
<typeStatus box="[491,588,1125,1149]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Daday" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[620,744,1125,1149]" class="Arachnida" family="Arrenuridae" genus="Arrenurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundus">
<emphasis box="[620,744,1125,1149]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">A. rotundus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is lodged in the Naturhistorisches Museum in Basel, but unfortunately the slide does not contain the specimen (Hänggi pers. comm.). 
<bibRefCitation author="Daday, E. von" box="[1222,1384,1160,1184]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" pagination="1 - 374" refId="ref7639" refString="Daday, E. von 1905. Untersuchungen uber die Susswasser-Mikrofauna Paraguays. Mit einem Anhang: Zur Kenntnis der Naididen von Dr. W. Michaelsen. Zoologica, 18: 1 - 374." type="journal article" year="1905">Daday’s (1905)</bibRefCitation>
illustrations are too sketchy or even erroneous to draw any conclusions. K. 
<bibRefCitation author="Viets, K." box="[1169,1309,1194,1218]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" pagination="161 - 247" refId="ref8570" refString="Viets, K. 1954 b. Wassermilben aus dem Amazonasgebiet (Hydrachnellae, Acari). (Systematsche und okologische Untersuchungen). Bearbeitung der Sammlungen Dr. R. Braun, und Dr. H. Sioli, Belem. Schweiz. Zschr. Hydrol., 16: 78 - 151, 16: 161 - 247. doi: 10.1007 / BF 02483636" type="journal article" year="1954">Viets (1954b)</bibRefCitation>
came to the same conclusion as 
<bibRefCitation author="Lundblad, O." box="[641,822,1229,1253]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" pagination="1 - 86" refId="ref7736" refString="Lundblad, O. 1930. Sudamerikanische Hydracarinen. Zugleich Revision einiger von E. Daday aus Paraguay beschriebenen Arten. Zool. Bidr. Uppsala, 13: 1 - 86." type="journal article" year="1930">Lundblad (1930)</bibRefCitation>
about the glandularia anterior and posterior to the genital plates. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Viets, K." box="[653,794,1263,1287]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" pagination="161 - 247" refId="ref8570" refString="Viets, K. 1954 b. Wassermilben aus dem Amazonasgebiet (Hydrachnellae, Acari). (Systematsche und okologische Untersuchungen). Bearbeitung der Sammlungen Dr. R. Braun, und Dr. H. Sioli, Belem. Schweiz. Zschr. Hydrol., 16: 78 - 151, 16: 161 - 247. doi: 10.1007 / BF 02483636" type="journal article" year="1954">Viets (1954b)</bibRefCitation>
the palp of 
<taxonomicName box="[914,1035,1263,1287]" class="Arachnida" family="Arrenuridae" genus="Arrenurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minimus">
<emphasis box="[914,1035,1263,1287]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">A. minimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has P5 with a distinctly downturned claw and the ventral seta of P4 is without a hook, while the palp 
<emphasis box="[1159,1178,1297,1321]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">A</emphasis>
of. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Daday" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[1189,1283,1297,1321]" class="Arachnida" family="Arrenuridae" genus="Arrenurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundus">
<emphasis box="[1189,1283,1297,1321]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">rotundus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the claw of P5 more obliquely orientated and the ventral seta of P4 is with a hook. Based on these differences it is clear that my specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[863,953,1366,1390]" name="Suriname" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">Surinam</collectingCountry>
belong to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Daday" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[1061,1184,1366,1390]" class="Arachnida" family="Arrenuridae" genus="Arrenurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundus">
<emphasis box="[1061,1184,1366,1390]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">A. rotundus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[491,1567,472,1665]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">
<bibRefCitation author="Rosso de Ferradas, B. E." box="[531,815,1401,1425]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" pagination="193 - 200" refId="ref8084" refString="Rosso de Ferradas, B. E. 1981 a. Acerca de los generos Dadayella, Koenike 1907 y Arrenurus, subgenero Truncaturus Thor, 1901, en el Parana medio (Republica Argentina) (Acari, Arrenuridae, Hydrachnellae). Rev. Soc. Ent. Argent., 40: 193 - 200." type="journal article" year="1981">Rosso de Ferradas (1981a)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. Viets" authorityYear="1954" box="[925,1019,1401,1425]" class="Arachnida" family="Arrenuridae" genus="Arrenurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanus">
<emphasis box="[925,1019,1401,1425]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">A. nanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1088,1208,1401,1425]" name="Argentina" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, but according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Cramer, C. &amp; Cook D. R." box="[1424,1504,1401,1425]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" refId="ref7586" refString="Cramer, C. &amp; Cook D. R. 1992. New species of Arrenurus (Dadayella) (Acari: Arrenuridae) from" type="book" year="1992">Cramer</bibRefCitation>
&amp; Cook (1992) the males must be assigned to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Daday" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[993,1118,1435,1459]" class="Arachnida" family="Arrenuridae" genus="Arrenurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundus">
<emphasis box="[993,1118,1435,1459]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">A. rotundus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the males reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rosso de Ferradas, B. E." box="[491,773,1469,1493]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" pagination="193 - 200" refId="ref8084" refString="Rosso de Ferradas, B. E. 1981 a. Acerca de los generos Dadayella, Koenike 1907 y Arrenurus, subgenero Truncaturus Thor, 1901, en el Parana medio (Republica Argentina) (Acari, Arrenuridae, Hydrachnellae). Rev. Soc. Ent. Argent., 40: 193 - 200." type="journal article" year="1981">Rosso de Ferradas (1981a)</bibRefCitation>
have a different configuration of the dorsal glandularia and setae (e.g. postocularia much closer to each other), differently shaped genital plates and antagonistic bristle without a hook, therefore they might belong to a different species. Unfortunately, I have not been able to examine these specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
